"**Comparison of Energy and Sustainability Policies: Ranil Wickremesinghe vs. Sajith Premadasa**\n\n| **Policy Area** | **Ranil Wickremesinghe** | **Sajith Premadasa** |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Renewable Energy | Invest in renewable energy production, aiming for 70% of power supply by 2030 | Exceed 70% renewable energy generation by 2030, making Sri Lanka a regional renewable energy powerhouse |\n| Green Energy Hub | Establish Sri Lanka as a Green Energy Hub, exporting energy to neighboring countries | No data available |\n| Natural Gas Power Generation | Increase natural gas power generation | No data available |\n| Reduced Energy Costs | Reduce energy costs for citizens | Reduce energy costs through transition to renewables, boosting economic growth and competitiveness |\n| Emission Trading Scheme | Introduce an emission trading scheme in line with international standards | No data available |\n| Carbon Tax | Introduce a carbon tax | No data available |\n| Environmental Sustainability | Operate production industries on an environmental-friendly basis | Update National Environmental Act of 1980 and other laws to ensure environmental protection |\n| Climate Change and Environmental Policies | Implement a comprehensive five-year action plan to address climate change and environmental policies | Integrate local communities and private sector, utilizing blue carbon credits and international funding for climate-resilient infrastructure |\n| Green Hydrogen Production | Invest in green hydrogen production | Pursue production of green hydrogen and invite direct foreign investments |\n\n**Common Policies:**\n\n* Both candidates aim to increase the use of renewable energy sources.\n* Both candidates prioritize reducing energy costs for citizens.\n* Both candidates emphasize the importance of environmental sustainability.\n\n**Unique or Innovative Policies:**\n\n* Ranil Wickremesinghe:\n\t+ Establishing Sri Lanka as a Green Energy Hub.\n\t+ Introducing an emission trading scheme and carbon tax.\n* Sajith Premadasa:\n\t+ Exceeding the target of 70% renewable energy generation by 2030.\n\t+ Pursuing regional energy connectivity arrangements.\n\n**Analysis:**\n\nRanil Wickremesinghe's policies focus on establishing Sri Lanka as a Green Energy Hub, reducing energy costs, and promoting environmental sustainability. His approach emphasizes the importance of international cooperation and adherence to global standards.\n\nSajith Premadasa's policies prioritize exceeding the target of 70% renewable energy generation by 2030 and making Sri Lanka a regional renewable energy powerhouse. His approach emphasizes the importance of regional energy connectivity and attracting foreign investments.\n\nOverall, both candidates prioritize renewable energy and environmental sustainability, but their approaches differ in terms of specific policies and targets."